name: Bunkbed
description: This wall is short so we had to get creative with our traverses. The very top of the rock is OFF ROUTE. Stand start on the obvious ledge left of the cave. Find a crimp above the ledge for the left and a decent ledge out to the right. This will allow you to lower your leg to an obvious ledge. From here match your left to your right and then go for the pinch deeper in the cave. From here use the obvious holds to reach the two flat protustions that look like bunk beds. Match the top bunk and then top out the boulder.   During the first ascent I somehow ending sitting criss-cross applesauce on on the “bottom bunk” before matching the final hold and topping out. I didn’t do that for fun, that was my legit beta.

name: Unnamed
description: This wall is short so we had to get creative with our traverses. The very top of the rock is OFF ROUTE. Start in a decent pocket near the top of the wall and reach down for a killer deep pocket (check it for critters first!). From there reach to another then cross over to a decent hold. Throw around the corner to a crimp and then establish your feet on a good ledge. Stand up on the ledge without using the top and you’re done.

name: A hole
description: Sit start below a small hole in center of boulder, up and over.. V hard. Never climbed

name: Azkabar
description: Triangle shaped boulder on the right side of a corridor on the far right end.  Start with hands at hip level, then up to the point at top.  Hard start leads to an easier finish

name: Big leg hair
description: Sit start at the left end of the boulder

name: Dunkey butt
description: Lay/ sit start way below in the little cave under the big mushroom shaped bulge on right side of boulder, move out to the bulge, then up and right towards the corner ,not straight up    No heel hooking on the Mushroom to make it harder

name: EZGB
description: Sit start at the left side of the big hole ..up and over

name: Flake up
description: Sit start below left end of flake in center of boulder.  Move up flake to your right, then up and over boulder at weakness before the corner      Variation:  Move to the end (corner) of the flake, straight up from corner    Both are fun..

name: Loungin
description: Sit start under big overhang on solo boulder with your left foot way up in the hole. Work up and over slopey roof above.  Powerful slopey moves..

name: Sloppy Arete
description: Sit start on decent holds on the bulge, feet straddling the arete. Slop onto a brutal sloper then reach up with the left to pockets. Bring your feet onto the starting hand hold and top out.

name: Slovak Traverse
description: Sit start/ lay start in the cave in front of the mushroom shaped bulge on right end, move up and left to the ridge/ top, then traverse left across the entire boulder.  Pumpy and long

name: Solo boulder
description: Small solitary boulder 15' in front of phenomenom boulder.  Sit start then up and over.. A few  awkward moves

name: Airtime
description: Scamper on top of the bridge support, stand up, then a reachy move to gain a small ledge. Use the crack or ledges top out on top of the bridge then walk down. This problem is in view of the park and has quite spectacular, airy moves.

name: Baby Version
description: Mantle up the side of the bridge with the help of a wall and big horizontal crack.

name: The Challenge
description: 50+ foot traverse hanging from slopers. The left side of the I-beam is textured while the right side is slick. Hasn’t been sent yet so the grade is an estimate. Nice pump fest for the end of the day, whoever gets the least furthest buys dinner.

name: Pinch
description: Right hand pinch the furthest right pinch, left hand pick your poison. Compression with your hands and tension with your legs gets you up to a decent crimp. From there throw to the ledge at the top. Hop the safety fence and walk down the path for official topout

name: Project
description: Start with hands on either side of the I-beam. Hook your foot on the park facing side and somehow find a way to mantle up. Reach up and around the roof for a small ledge. Pull the roof and top out on top of the bridge. Currently unsent but we think it's around a V6.

name: Sloppy's Boat
description: Use the textured blocks to gain a good ledge. From here, left hand grabs the vertical ledge and right hand grabs the vertical slope. Walk your feet up the blocks until you can reach the topout ledge. Hop the fence and walk down the path for official topout.

name: Sloppy's Ship
description: Use the large blocks to gain a small ledge and then lock and load on some vertical compression slopers. Walk up the blocks until you can reach the top ledge. Hop the fence and walk down the path for official topout.

name: Unnamed V0
description: Start just under the bridge below a shelf. Once your hands are on the shelf, trend left around the arete and finish climbing the face above the footpath. Be prepared to make a new friend as you pop up on the bridge walking path.

name: 50 Is The New 30
description: Approximately 12 feet high, overhanging route, the crux is toping out, walk off/down climb the back of the boulder.  Watch your step on the moss. Flat landing area.

name: Anvil's Lip Traverse
description: Start on the left side of the boulder that is shaped like an anvil's horn.  Cross the lip of the anvil and continue to the right a few moves then top out.

name: Does This Make My Butt Look Big
description: Super fun one move wonder. The problem begins with a high right heel hook. Walk off to the right.

name: Egyptian Wuss
description: Easy warm up climb. Crux is the footwork needed to get started on the boulder

name: Ham Hock Traverse
description: Really fun  traverse.  The route travels the length of the wall from the obvious crack on the left side all the way to the end of the horizontal hand crack next to "Lichen This Better". Balance and creativity is necessary as you traverse the wall utilizing monopockets, micro side pulls, finger cracks and solid but blind foot placements.

name: The Jerry Russ Route
description: Hand crack that widdens to a fist crack. Crimps for the left hand.

name: The Joke Is On Me
description: The sit start is the crux followed by a mantle.

name: The Joke is On You
description: Sit start with the crux being the super fun mantle.

name: The Last Dab
description: The sit start is the crux.  Reach up and right to get off the ground.

name: Lichen This Better
description: The crux is finding a left foot to reach up to a giant right hand side pull.  Trusting your feet on the lichen encrusted wall requires and adventuresome spirit.  Warm up on this route and the route to the right of it.  "Not really Lichen this"

name: Not Lichen This
description: Slabby, dirty, easy, juggy, walk off right Decent place to warm up.

name: Stumble Wise Slab
description: This slab has numerous opportunities to practice your footwork to prepare for those North Carolina slab routes that you want to do.  It is approximately 10 yards long and 10 feet high.  Pick a section and work it.  Try it no hands as well.  The footholds are mostly indentations in the rock with a few tiny ledges.  Have fun!

name: Turtle Neck
description: Start on Turtle Boulder behind the nose. Crimps and pockets to the top.  Down climb at the end of the boulder.

name: Turtle Nose
description: Sit start. Pull onto typical Tishomingo crimps. Climb out to the side of the nose for the top out.  Down Climb the other end of this boulder.

name: Veasy Slab
description: A great slab route that is sort of steep but easy enough to learn how to get your head into the game.  The crux is right before the top out.  Walk right and do the easy down climb to get off the boulder.

name: Walk Like An Egytian
description: Pyramid shaped slab with small foot holds and crimps.  Climb up the center of the boulder to the apex. The Crux is the reach after getting established on the slab. Scramble down the back of the boulder.

name: 104. Face
description: Tishomingo Face Climbing

name: Cabin #3 Corner
description: Corner of the Chimney

name: Cabin #3 Offwidth Chimney
description: Offwidth Chimney

name: Cabin #3 Offwidth Crack
description: Off Width Crack

name: Chimney #101
description: Chimney climbing.

name: Cleavage Crack
description: Off width crack

name: Corner
description: Climb outside corner

name: Denise's Dilema
description: Get your off width on in one of the many off width crack problems at Tishomingo.

name: Left Arete
description: Climb up the left edge.

name: Lost On Face
description: Face Climb

name: Offwidth Crack 96
description: Another off width crack

name: Dana's Overhang
description: Start in the dihedral just right of Jean's Overhang. Traverse right to a shelf. Turn the roof by pulling up on tiny face holds.

name: Jean's Overhang
description: "Tishomingo's finest route" overhanging fist crack

name: Mental Block
description: Don't let the mental block get to you.  The crux is transitioning from the first few moves to the face. The route ascends a short fist sized crack up onto the face where you follow a flake to the top. The protection is good and it also can be top roped. The vegetation at the top of the route is pretty dense so a top out would require some additional effort.  Good trees for a top rope setup are a bit far away.

name: Tishomingo Chop
description: Starts deep in the overhang. Make sure your pinch game is on point before making your way through this problem using face holds and hand jams to get to the top out.
